recipeData.name: Bacon Omelette
recipeData.ingredientList: eggs, cherry tomatoes, spinach, mushrooms, bacon, butter
recipeData.instructions: Beat the eggs in a small bowl until smooth. Heat the pan and melt the butter. Once melted, sautee the spinach, mushrooms, tomatoes, and diced bacon for 2 minutes. Then add the eggs to the pan and reduce to low heat. Once the eggs are nearly set, fold the omelette and turn off the heat.

recipeData.name: Spam Musubi
recipeData.ingredientList: rice, spam, seaweed
recipeData.instructions: Fry spam for 2 minutes on each side.  Mold the rice and cut seaweed. Assemble by placing spam on top of the rice, then wrapping it with seaweed.

recipeData.name: Creamy Pesto Penne with Sausage
recipeData.ingredientList: penne pasta, ground sausage, creamy pesto sauce, milk, olive oil
recipeData.instructions:
Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook penne at a boil, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 11 minutes; drain and transfer pasta to a bowl.
Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook and stir sausage in the hot skillet until browned and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes; add to pasta.
Whisk pesto sauce mix, milk, and olive oil together in a small saucepan; bring to a boil while stirring constantly. Reduce heat to low and keep at a simmer until thickened, about 3 minutes; pour over pasta and sausage mixture and toss to coat.

recipeData.name: Avocado Sandwich
recipeData.ingredientList: bread, provolone cheese, avocados, tomatoes, balsamic vinegar
recipeData.instructions: Lay 1 slice bread on a plate. Place provolone cheese on bread and top with avocado and tomato slices, respectively. Drizzle balsamic vinegar over tomato and top with remaining slice of bread.

recipeData.name: Pork and Peanut Dragon Noodles
recipeData.ingredientList: chili garlic sauce, soy sauce, brown sugar, ground pork, ramen noodles, green onions, unsalted peanuts
recipeData.instructions:
Combine the chili garlic sauce, soy sauce, and brown sugar in a bowl.
Add the ground pork to a skillet and cook over medium heat until it is fully browned*. Once browned, add the prepared dragon sauce and chopped peanuts. Allow the pork and peanuts to simmer in the sauce for another 5 minutes, or until the sauce has reduced by half.
While the pork is browning, begin boiling water for your noodles. Once boiling, add your noodles and cook according to the package directions. Drain the noodles in a colander.
Once the sauce has reduced and the noodles have drained, add the noodles to the skillet and toss until everything is combined and coated in sauce. Top with sliced green onions and serve!

recipeData.name: Pesto Chicken and Vegetables
recipeData.ingredientList: red bell pepper, zucchini, yellow squash, red onion, boneless chicken breast, cooking oil, green beans, pesto, salt, pepper, parmesan
recipeData.instructions:
Chop the bell pepper, yellow squash, and zucchini, and slice the red onion. I like to make different shapes for each vegetable, but aim to make the pieces all around the same size.
Cube the chicken breasts into ½-inch pieces.
Add the cooking oil to a large skillet and heat over medium-high. Once the skillet and oil are very hot, add the chicken and sauté until the chicken pieces are opaque (3-5 minutes – the chicken will continue to cook as you add vegetables).
Add the green beans to the skillet and sauté for 1-2 minutes more, or just until thawed.
Add the bell pepper and red onion to the skillet. Sauté for 1-2 minutes more. If water is beginning to pool in the skillet, turn the heat up slightly. It should be hot enough that the water released from the vegetables evaporates quickly.
Add the yellow squash and zucchini to the skillet and continue to sauté 2-3 minutes more, or just until the squash softens slightly.
Turn the heat off, add the pesto to the skillet, and stir until everything is coated. Give the vegetables a taste and add salt, pepper, or more pesto if desired. Top with a light sprinkle of Parmesan just before serving.

recipeData.name: Top Ramen
recipeData.ingredientList: instant ramen
recipeData.instructions: Pour boiling water into the cup of instant ramen. Cover and wait for 2 minutes.

recipeData.name: Curried Chickpeas with Spinach
recipeData.ingredientList: olive oil, yellow onion, garlic, ginger, curry powder, spinach, tomato sauce, chickpeas
recipeData.instructions:
Dice the onion, mince the garlic, and grate the ginger on a small holed cheese grater. Sauté the onion, garlic, and ginger in a large skillet with the olive oil over medium heat until the onions have softened (3-5 minutes).
Add the curry powder and continue to sauté with the onion mixture for one minute more. Add about 1/4 cup of water to the skillet along with the fresh spinach and continue to sauté until the spinach has wilted. The water will help steam and wilt the spinach (no water needed if using frozen spinach).
Drain and rinse the chickpeas. Add them to the skillet along with the tomato sauce. Stir well to distribute the spices in the sauce and heat through (5 minutes). Serve over rice or with bread.

recipeData.name: Vegan Creamy Mushroom Ramen
recipeData.ingredientList: cooking oil, baby bella mushrooms, vegetable broth, spinach, ramen noodles, coconut milk, green onions, chili garlic sauce
recipeData.instructions:
Slice the mushrooms. Add them to a small sauce pot with the cooking oil and sauté over medium heat until the mushrooms are soft, dark, and all the moisture in the bottom of the pot has evaporated.
Add the vegetable broth, turn the heat up to medium-high, and bring the broth up to a boil. Once boiling, add the ramen noodles (without the seasoning packet) to the broth. Cook the noodles in the boiling broth for about 3 minutes, or until tender.
Turn the heat off, add a heaping handful of fresh spinach, and stir until the spinach is wilted (about 30 seconds). Pour the coconut milk into the pot and stir to combine.
Serve the Vegan Creamy Coconut Ramen as-is, or with garnishes like green onion or chili garlic sauce.

recipeData.name: Hearty Black Bean Quesadillas
recipeData.ingredientList: black beans, corn, red onion, garlic, cilantro, cheddar cheese, taco seasoning, flour tortillas
recipeData.instructions:
Drain the black beans and add them to a bowl along with the frozen corn (no need to thaw)
Finely dice the onion, mince the garlic, and roughly chop the cilantro.
Add the onion, garlic, cilantro, shredded cheddar, and taco seasoning to the bowl with the beans and corn. Stir until everything is evenly combined and coated in seasoning.
Place a half cup of the filling on one side of each tortilla and fold over. Cook the quesadillas in a skillet over medium heat on each side until brown and crispy and the cheesy filling has melted. Slice into triangles then serve.
To freeze the quesadillas, stack the filled and uncooked quesadillas with a piece of parchment paper between each quesadilla. Place in a freezer bag and freeze for up to three months. To reheat either microwave (for a soft quesadilla) or cook in a skillet on low heat (make sure to use low heat so that the filling has time to thaw and melt before the outside burns).

recipeData.name: Pizzadillas
recipeData.ingredientList: flour tortillas, mozzarella, pepperoni, bell peppers, red onions, black olives, mushrooms, pizza sauce
recipeData.instructions:
Prep the ingredients by thinly slicing the vegetables and draining the olives and mushrooms.
For each pizzadilla: Measure 1/3 cup of shredded cheese. Sprinkle half of the cheese over one half of the tortilla, add toppings and then sprinkle the rest of the cheese on top. Fold the empty side of the tortilla over the toppings.
Place the pizzadilla in a prewarmed skillet (medium heat) and cook until brown and crispy on the bottom. Carefully flip the pizzadilla over and cook until brown and crispy on the second side. Once both sides are crisp and the cheese is melted inside, slice into thirds with a pizza cutter. Dip in the pizza sauce prior to eating.

recipeData.name: Pizza Roll Ups
recipeData.ingredientList: flour tortillas, pepperoni, mozzarella cheese sticks, oil, pizza sauce
recipeData.instructions:
Preheat the oven to 400ºF. Lightly spritz a baking sheet with spray oil or brush a thin layer of your favorite cooking oil onto the baking sheet.
Stack about 4 tortillas at a time on a plate and cover with a damp paper towel. Microwave for 20-30 seconds, or until they are steamy and pliable. Microwave the second batch when you're ready to roll more.
Slice each of the mozzarella sticks in half, lengthwise. Place about 5 pepperoni on each tortilla in the bottom 1/3 o the circle, then place the halved mozzarella stick on top. Fold the sides of the tortilla in to cover the ends, then roll them up tight light a burrito.
Place the tightly rolled Pizza Roll Ups on the baking sheet, seam side down. Leave them slightly apart from one another to allow hot air to surround the rolls. Either spritz the top with spray oil, or brush a thin layer of oil on top of the roll ups.
Bake the Pizza Roll Ups for 12-15 minutes, or until they're lightly browned and the cheese is just beginning to ooze. Because every oven is different, begin checking on the Pizza Roll Ups at about 10 minutes, then check ever two minutes or so until they're done.
Serve immediately, with pizza sauce for dipping.

recipeData.name: Homemade Freezer Garlic Bread
recipeData.ingredientList: salted butter, olive oil, garlic, garlic powder, salt, dried parsley, French bread
recipeData.instructions:
Add the butter, olive oil, minced garlic, garlic powder, salt, and parsley to a bowl. Mix the ingredients together until they form a fairly smooth mixture.
Slice the French bread into 1-inch thick slices (12-16 slices, depending on the size of the loaf). Add 1/2 to 1 Tbsp of the garlic spread to each slice of bread and spread it from edge to edge. Arrange the slices on a baking sheet and then place them in the freezer for about 30 minutes to allow the butter to firm up. Once firm, transfer the garlic bread to a gallon-sized freezer bag for longer storage. Store in the freezer up to three months.
To cook the frozen slices of garlic bread, preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Once the oven is heated, take as many slices out of the freezer as you'd like, and place them on a baking sheet. Bake for 10-15 minutes, or until the edges are golden brown.* If you prefer a softer garlic bread without crispy edges, wrap the slices in foil before baking.

recipeData.name: Avocado Toast
recipeData.ingredientList: bread, avocados, parsley, olive oil, lemon, salt, pepper, garlic powder
recipeData.instructions: Toast the bread. Scoop the avocado into a bowl. Add the parsley, olive oil, lemon, salt, pepper, and garlic powder to the avocado and mix together. Spread the mixture on the pieces of toast.

recipeData.name: Baked Potato
recipeData.ingredientList: potatoes, salt, pepper, butter, cheese, sour cream
recipeData.instructions: Scrub potato and prick holes with a fork. Microwave for 5 minutes. Turn potato over and microwave for an additional 5 minutes. Cut potato in half lengthwise and season with salt and pepper. Mash up the inside of the potato with a fork. Add the butter and cheese. Microwave the potato for 1 minute. Top with sour cream.

recipeData.name: Salted Chocolate-Peanut Butter Vegan Nice Cream
recipeData.ingredientList: cashews, bananas, tofu, cacao powder, dates, peanut butter, vanilla extract, soy milk, salt, peanuts
recipeData.instructions: Soak cashews in a bowl of water for 1-3 hours, Drain. Combine the cashews with 1 banana, 1 cup of ice cubes, 3 ounces of tofu, 1/2 cup of cacao powder, 2 pitted dates, 3 tablespoons of peanut butter, 2 teaspoons of vanilla extract, 1 teaspoon of soy milk, and 1/4 teaspoon of sea salt. Blend until smooth. When finished, sprinkle with crushed peanuts.

recipeData.name: Toasted Cheese Sandwich
recipeData.ingredientList: Cheese, bread rolls, sugar
recipeData.instructions: Top each bread roll with some cheese. Toast the rolls in a toaster oven until cheese is melted, about 5 to 7 minutes. Sprinkle sugar over the melted cheese to taste.

recipeData.name: Carbonara
recipeData.ingredientList: spaghetti, bacon, eggs, parmesan, olive oil
recipeData.instructions: Bring a pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook spaghetti for 8 to 10 minutes. Drain water. Place 1 pound of chopped bacon into a skillet and cook until evenly brown. Place spaghetti in a large bowl and add in 1/4 cup of olive oil. Stir in bacon, 4 beaten eggs, and 3/4 cup of parmesan cheese.

recipeData.name: Beef Stroganoff
recipeData.ingredientList: egg noodles, ground beef, cream of mushroom soup, garlic powder, sour cream, pepper
recipeData.instructions: Cook 1 pound of ground beef until browned. Bring a pot of lightly salted water to a boil and cook egg noodles for 7 to 9 minutes. Drain water. Stir 1 can of cream of mushroom soup and garlic powder into the ground beef. Simmer for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and add egg noodles. Stir in 1/2 a cup of sour cream and season with salt and pepper.

recipeData.name: Pork Chops
recipeData.ingredientList: italian salad dressing, soy sauce, pepper, pork chops
recipeData.instructions: Mix 2 cups of the italian salad dressing, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and 1/4 coup of soy sauce in a bowl. Place 4 boneless pork chops int a skillet over medium high heat. Cover with the dressing mixture. Cover skillet and cook for 25 minutes, turning occasionally. Remove cover, reduce heat, and cook until done.

recipeData.name: Sloppy Joes
recipeData.ingredientList: ground turkey, ketchup, sugar, vinegar, mustard
recipeData.instructions: Cook 1 pound of ground turkey until evenly brown. In a large saucepan over medium heat, mix 1 cup of ketchup, 2 tablespoons of sugar, 2 tablespoons of vinegar, and 2 tablespoons of mustard. Mix in the turkey. Cook for 30 minutes, serving occasionally. Serve with buns.

recipeData.name: Peanut Butter Mousse
recipeData.ingredientList: peanut butter, greek yogurt, brown sugar, vanilla extract, chocolate chips
recipeData.instructions: Microwave 2 tablespoons of peanut butter until liquid and smooth. Stir in 1/4 cup of plain greek yogurt until smooth. Stir in 1/2 teaspoon of brown sugar and 1/8 teaspoon of vanilla extract. Fold in chocolate chips

recipeData.name: Red Curry Chicken
recipeData.ingredientList: coconut oil, chicken breast, cream of coconut, red thai curry sauce, vermicelli noodles
recipeData.instructions: Heat up oil on high. Cut chicken breasts into cubes and cook until browned. Reduce heat and add 1 can of cream of coconut and 1 bottle of red Thai curry sauce. Cook for an additional 5 minutes. Fill another pot with lightly salted water and cook vermicelli pasta. Drain water. Reduce chicken curry to a simmer. Add noodles and simmer for about 5 minutes.

recipeData.name: Arugula and Hummus Mini Pizzas
recipeData.ingredientList: humus, naan bread, arugula, date, pumpkin seeds, balsamic vinegar
recipeData.instructions: Spread hummus onto naan bread; top with arugula, date, and pumpkin seeds. Drizzle balsamic vinegar over pizza.

recipeData.name: Steamy Microwave Zucchini
recipeData.ingredientList: zucchini, celery, onion, mushrooms, cheddar cheese
recipeData.instructions: Mix zucchini, celery, onion, and mushrooms in a microwave-safe dish. Cover dish with plastic wrap.Cook on High until vegetables are steamed and slightly tender, about 6 minutes.Pull plastic wrap away from dish, stir vegetables, sprinkle Cheddar cheese over the vegetables, and replace the plastic to seal tightly. Let dish sit until the cheese melts, 2 to 3 minutes. Stir vegetables to coat evenly with melted cheese.

recipeData.name: Creamy Blueberry Coconut Ricotta Bowl
recipeData.ingredientList: ricotta cheese, coconut milk, honey, slivered almonds, flaked coconut, blueberries
recipeData.instructions: Combine ricotta cheese and coconut milk in a bowl. Drizzle on honey and sprinkle with almonds and coconut. Top with blueberries.

recipeData.name: Roasted Green Beans
recipeData.ingredientList: green beans, olive oil, salt, pepper
recipeData.instructions: Drizzle the clean and trimmed green beans with olive oil, then season them evenly with salt and pepper. Roast in a preheated oven until the beans look crisp.

recipeData.name: Creamy Parmesan Polenta
recipeData.ingredientList: polenta, chicken broth, parmesan cheese, black pepper, paprika
recipeData.instructions: Stir polenta and chicken broth together in a saucepan over medium heat; cook and stir until the polenta is heated through completely, about 5 minutes.Remove pan from heat. Stir Parmesan cheese, black pepper, and paprika with the polenta mixture.

recipeData.name: Macaroni and Cheese
recipeData.ingredientList: macaroni, butter, flour, salt, black pepper, milk, shredded cheddar cheese
recipeData.instructions: Bring a large pot of water to boil and add a pinch of salt to the water. Add in macaroni and follow box instructions for cooking and drain once done. Melt butter in a separate saucepan and mix together flour, salt, and pepper until smooth for around 5 minutes. Add in milk slowly while stirring until smooth. Add in cheddar cheese to the mixture until melted. Then combine the pasta and cheese sauce together.

recipeData.name: Baked Chicken Wings
recipeData.ingredientList: chicken wings, olive oil, garlic, chili powder, garlic powder, salt, black pepper
recipeData.instructions: Preheat your oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit. Combine chicken wings, olive oil, and garlic into a mixing bowl. In a separate bowl, mix chili powder, garlic powder, salt, and black pepper together then pour over the chicken and mix thoroughly. Place chicken on a baking sheet and cook chicken wings in the oven for about an hour or until crisp and cooked through.

recipeData.name: Baked Parmesan Chicken
recipeData.ingredientList: chicken breast, garlic, bread crumbs, parmesan cheese, dried basil, black pepper
recipeData.instructions: Preheat your oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit. Mince your garlic and combine it with the olive oil and place it in a bowl. In a separate bowl, combine the bread crumbs, parmesan cheese, dried basil, and pepper. Dip the chicken breast in the oil mixture, then in the bread crumb mixture. Once all the chicken is coated in breadcrumbs, arrange on a baking sheet and place in the oven to cook for 30 minutes.

recipeData.name: Vegetarian Taco Casserole
recipeData.ingredientList: tortilla chips, vegetarian chili, cheddar cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, salsa, sour cream
recipeData.instructions: Preheat your oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit. In a baking dish, cover the bottom with tortilla chips and pour vegetarian chili and cheese on top. Bake in the oven for 25 minutes until chili and cheese is heated through. Top with lettuce, tomato, salsa, and sour cream once out of the oven and enjoy.

recipeData.name: Peanut Butter Banana Oatmeal
recipeData.ingredientList: oats, water, salt, banana, peanut butter, vanilla extract
recipeData.instructions: Heat up water and salt in a pot and stir in oats once boiling. Once the oats thicken up, remove from heat and combine with banana, peanut butter, and vanilla extract.

recipeData.name: Roasted Carrots
recipeData.ingredientList: carrots, thyme, olive oil, honey, salt
recipeData.instructions: Preheat your oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit. Slice carrots into thin slices and place on a baking tray and brush the carrots with a mixture of oil, honey, salt, and thyme. Roast carrots for 20-25 minutes until tender.

recipeData.name: Roasted Cauliflower
recipeData.ingredientList: cauliflower, olive oil, rosemary, salt
recipeData.instructions: Preheat your oven to 450 degrees Fahrenheit. Chop up cauliflower into large chunks and toss together with olive oil, rosemary, and salt. Then place on baking tray and roast in the oven for 20-25 minutes.

recipeData.name: Cauliflower Mash
recipeData.ingredientList: cauliflower, chicken broth, garlic, black pepper, bay leaf, salt
recipeData.instructions: Combine chicken broth, garlic, black pepper, bay leaf, and salt in a pot to boil. Once boiling, strain the garlic and bay leaf and remove from heat. Place cauliflower in a large pot of boiling water until tender and add it to the other pot of seasoned chicken broth. Mash until desired consistency.

recipeData.name: Guacamole
recipeData.ingredientList: avocado, lemon juice, salsa, salt
recipeData.instructions: Peel and chop avocados and place into a small bowl. Mash together while combining with lemon juice, salsa, and salt. Place in the fridge to chill before serving.

recipeData.name: Caprese Salad Kabobs
recipeData.ingredientList: cherry tomato, mozzarella, basil, olive oil, balsamic vinegar
recipeData.instructions: On skewers, thread together tomatoes, mozzarella, and basil leaves alternating between each ingredient. Combine olive oil and balsamic vinegar together and drizzle over kabobs.
